From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] lctech: ramoops/pstore carveout for lockup triage

The board hard-hangs silently (serial + SysRq dead) under sustained
video decode on 7.1.x, with BOTH cedar and cedrus, CMA relocation and
DRAM memtest clean. Reserve 512 KiB below the top MiB of DRAM for
ramoops so the console log and (optionally) the function trace survive
the watchdog reset and name the code that was running at the wedge.

Triage-only; drop together with the linux.fragment debug block when
the lockup is closed.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts | 27 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
@@ -328,3 +328,30 @@
 		};
 	};
 };
+
+/*
+ * Lockup triage: persistent oops/console/ftrace store surviving a watchdog
+ * reset. 512 KiB just below the top MiB of DRAM (top ~56 KiB holds U-Boot's
+ * relocated FDT). The default (non-fixed) CMA reservation moves itself below
+ * this carveout automatically. Read after reboot:
+ *   mount -t pstore pstore /sys/fs/pstore && cat /sys/fs/pstore/*
+ * Function-trace-to-pstore for the final word before death:
+ *   echo 1 > /sys/kernel/debug/pstore/record_ftrace
+ */
+&{/} {
+	reserved-memory {
+		#address-cells = <1>;
+		#size-cells = <1>;
+		ranges;
+
+		ramoops@83e00000 {
+			compatible = "ramoops";
+			reg = <0x83e00000 0x80000>;
+			console-size = <0x20000>;
+			record-size = <0x8000>;
+			ftrace-size = <0x20000>;
+			pmsg-size = <0x0>;
+			ecc-size = <16>;
+		};
+	};
+};
